      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Choline, a component of the phospholipids in cell membranes, can be prepared by S<sub>N</sub>2 reaction of trimethylamine with ethylene oxide. Show the structure of choline, and propose a mechanism for the reaction.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaVFaIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--c022f40b45f9fb730a9d64c842bf50a3ca7f4a9c/OChem_24_EC_025.jpg\" alt=\"Trimethylamine reacts with ethylene oxide to produce choline, which has an unknown structure.\">",
